# Self-Play Workflow Rules

This project uses controlled self-play:

Customer ↔ Support Agent ↔ Orchestrator ↔ Judge

Rules:

- The orchestrator controls turn order
- Only one speaker per turn
- No direct agent-to-agent hidden communication
- Ground truth is accessible ONLY to customer simulator
- Support agent must infer intent via dialogue

Turn structure must be:

1. Agent generates structured JSON
2. Orchestrator validates
3. Customer generates structured JSON
4. Orchestrator validates
5. Repeat until stop condition

Stop conditions must always be checked after each turn.

Never allow free-form infinite conversation.